<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ871118-0147 </DOCNO><HL> Business Brief:CCC Information Services Inc.</HL><DD> 11/18/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> CARXTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><TEXT>   CCC Information Services Inc. said it reached a definitive agreement to be acquired for $9 a share, or about $79.2 million, by closely held Financial Protection Services Inc.    Chicago-based CCC, which advises insurance companies on the value of automobiles, said its directors approved the offer and have agreed to tender their shares. The offer is subject to financing and the tender of at least 51% of its 8.8 million common shares outstanding. In national over-the-counter trading yesterday, CCC closed at $8.25 a share, up $2.    Financial Protection, Springfield, Va., is a credit-card registration service, among other things.    For 1986, CCC earned $2.2 million, or 29 cents a share, on revenue of $13.8 million. It said it received a favorable fairness opinion on the offer from Hambrecht andamp; Quist Inc., an investment firm. CCC said Financial Protection has retained Sutro andamp; Co. and First Boston Corp. to arrange financing.    The pact follows the cancellation in October of CCC's agreement to be acquired in a stock swap by Fort Lauderdale, Fla.-based SafeCard Services Inc., a credit-card registration service. </TEXT></DOC>